conclusion: Reconsidered the proportionality of F to n and identified it as not exact.
Derived a theoretical formula F = 10μ × (1 - 1/n) but found it doesn't match smaller n values.
Tried a different formula F = μW(n/2) but found it doesn't match the data points.
Reconsidered and used F = μW(n-1)/2 but found it still doesn't match the data.
Reanalyzed and used F = μWn/2, leading to the correct value of μ = 0.6.
